ESCALATION TRIGGERS: 1. Circuit breaker trips (3x FIX on same dimension) 2. Same dimension fails consecutively 2x 3. Human explicitly requests escalation 4. Conflicting SSOT change request 5. Ethical guardrail concern
ESCALATION PACKET: { "escalation_id": "esc-001", "trigger": "circuit_breaker", "context": { "asset_id": "sp-001", "dimension": "proof_discipline", "fix_attempts": 3, "last_scores": [6.5, 7.0, 6.8], "correction_log": [...] }, "options": [ {"action": "approve_as_is", "risk": "Proof gaps remain"}, {"action": "force_loop", "risk": "May not improve"}, {"action": "patch_skill", "risk": "Skill update needed"}, {"action": "stop", "risk": "Asset incomplete"} ], "recommendation": "patch_skill", "reasoning": "Repeated failures suggest skill gap, not content issue" }
HUMAN DECISION CAPTURE: - Log decision with timestamp and rationale - If patch approved, generate PATCH_PROPOSAL - If override approved, log risk acceptance - Continue or stop based on decision

